name: ContraceptivePatchICD10CMProvisionEncounters
title: Contraceptive Patch ICD10CM Provision Encounters
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Family planning - provision and use of most and moderately effective contraceptive methods),(Data Element Scope: Diagnosis codes indicating prescription or provision of contraceptive patch, a moderately effective method of contraception),(Inclusion Criteria: Diagnosis codes indicating prescription or provision of contraceptive patch, a moderately effective method of contraception),(Exclusion Criteria: Any contraceptive method that is not a contraceptive patch; Most effective (i.e., sterilization, contraceptive implants, intrauterine devices or systems) or moderately effective (i.e., injectables, oral pills, or ring) methods of contraception; Less effective methods of contraception (i.e., diaphragm, male condom, female condom, withdrawal, sponge, fertility-awareness based methods, spermicide))
